HEADWORD: Neuropodous
<hw>Neu*rop"o*dous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Neuro-</ets> + <ets>-pod</ets> + <ets>-ous</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the limbs on, or directed toward, the
neural side, as in most invertebrates; -- opposed to
<ant>haemapodous</ant>.</def> <rj><au>G. Rolleston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
